# Vectro v2.1 Backlog [ARCHIVED]

**⚠️ NOTE: This file is archived. The items listed below were targeted for v2.1 but have been implemented as part of v3.0.0+**

All items marked "High Priority" and "Medium Priority" below have been completed and shipped in v3.x releases:
- INT4 Stability → GA in v3.0.0
- AsyncIO Streaming → not yet (backlog item)
- Milvus Connector → shipped in v3.1.0
- Chroma Connector → shipped in v3.1.0
- ONNX Export → shipped in v3.2.0
- vectro info --benchmark → shipped in v3.3.0

This file is retained for historical reference only. For current roadmap, see [VECTRO_V3_PLAN.md](VECTRO_V3_PLAN.md) and [PLAN.md](PLAN.md).

---

## 🥇 High Priority [COMPLETED in v3.x]

### INT4 Stability (Experimental → General Availability) ✅
- ✅ Removed the `enable_experimental_precisions=True` guard on INT4 mode
- ✅ Validated quality gates at INT4 across all standard embedding dimensions (128, 384, 768, 1536)
- ✅ Added INT4 to the profile selector in `ProfileManager`
- ✅ Updated CI matrix with `precision=int4` regression lane

### AsyncIO Streaming Decompressor 🔄
- ⏳ `AsyncStreamingDecompressor` — `async for chunk in AsyncStreamingDecompressor(result)`
- ⏳ Compatible with `asyncio` event loops and `trio`
- ⏳ Documents backpressure semantics and `chunk_size` tuning

### Milvus Connector ✅
- ✅ `python/integrations/milvus_connector.py` — `MilvusConnector`
- ✅ `store_batch(vectors, ids, metadata)` → collection upsert
- ✅ `search(query_vec, top_k)` → ranked results
- ✅ Shipped in v3.1.0

### `vectro info --benchmark` Quick Bench Flag ✅
- ✅ Added `vectro info --benchmark` that runs a 5-second throughput estimation
- ✅ Shipped in v3.3.0

---

